A NEW networking group for property investors is being launched in Glasgow. Investors pin hopes on new group A NEW networking group for property investors is being launched in Glasgow.Councillor Philip Braat, director of the West Scotland Loans Fund, will launch the first Glasgow 'pin' meeting on September 24.The event, at the Thistle Hotel, is expected to attract landlords, investors and property entrepreneurs.Event host Louis Stedman-Bryce, said: &quot;I am absolutely delighted to be hosting the first of what will become a regular monthly event in Glasgow. pin is a great environment where people share ideas and experiences for the benefit of everyone who attends.&quot;It is being held from 6-9pm and tickets are available from www.pinmeeting.co.uk/glasgow. 